WEBVTT

00:07.357 --> 00:12.357
Subtitles by explosiveskull
www.OpenSubtitles.org

01:53.413 --> 01:54.414
10 please.

01:58.585 --> 02:00.188
I like your costume.

02:00.220 --> 02:03.457
Thanks, I was going to cosplay
as Urahara from "Bleach",

02:03.490 --> 02:05.026
but I couldn't
find the right hat.

02:05.059 --> 02:06.994
I tried to dye
green streaks in it,

02:07.028 --> 02:08.930
but then the whole
thing turned green,

02:08.963 --> 02:10.764
so I went with Naruto instead.

02:33.721 --> 02:35.555
Mister Nimoy?

02:37.692 --> 02:38.960
Mister Nimoy?

02:40.962 --> 02:42.063
Mister Nimoy?

02:44.031 --> 02:45.199
Mister Nimoy?

03:35.249 --> 03:36.117
Shit.

03:37.551 --> 03:38.451
Hello?

03:38.485 --> 03:39.854
Heather, Your brother's here.

03:43.257 --> 03:44.524
Uncle Jeffrey.

03:44.558 --> 03:45.592
Uncle Jeffrey.

03:45.626 --> 03:47.195
I'm your Uncle, I want respect.

03:48.395 --> 03:50.463
Okay look, I brought
toys for you, look.

03:50.497 --> 03:53.366
This, I just directed that,
okay you can have that one.

03:53.400 --> 03:54.302
No fighting.

03:54.334 --> 03:56.771
This one I just voiced, okay.

03:56.804 --> 03:59.539
And this one I voiced,
wrote and directed.

03:59.573 --> 04:01.709
You don't care, goodbye.

04:01.742 --> 04:02.710
Hi.

04:02.743 --> 04:03.945
Hey, how's it going Heather?

04:03.978 --> 04:05.246
Hey buddy.

04:05.279 --> 04:06.280
What buddy?

04:06.314 --> 04:07.514
I don't want any books.

04:07.547 --> 04:08.582
Okay.

04:08.616 --> 04:10.251
I have to feed the baby,
we'll catch up later.

04:10.284 --> 04:11.786
All right, I'll talk
to you later, bye.

04:12.452 --> 04:14.387
Hey Rob, what's up?

04:14.421 --> 04:15.823
Hey, dinner's almost ready.

04:15.857 --> 04:19.160
Cool, hey can I talk
to you afterwards?

04:19.192 --> 04:20.027
For a minute?

04:22.830 --> 04:24.497
Okay, good talk.

04:29.337 --> 04:31.239
I can't, I
just don't have it.

04:32.405 --> 04:33.975
Just to get
me through the summer.

04:34.008 --> 04:36.010
What about NFL Films?

04:36.043 --> 04:37.645
You won an Emmy with them.

04:37.678 --> 04:39.146
Surely they can find
something for you.

04:39.180 --> 04:41.481
That was 20 years ago.

04:41.514 --> 04:43.718
Everyone I know there is gone,

04:43.751 --> 04:44.551
or dead.

04:46.087 --> 04:47.989
Just go back to anime.

04:48.022 --> 04:49.991
You're a superstar
in that world.

04:50.024 --> 04:51.826
Actor, writer, director.

04:51.859 --> 04:52.760
Jeff Nimoy.

04:54.662 --> 04:56.163
Yeah.

04:56.197 --> 04:57.597
It's complicated.

04:57.632 --> 04:59.066
It's complicated?

04:59.100 --> 05:00.601
You know what else
is complicated?

05:00.635 --> 05:01.969
My checkbook's complicated.

05:03.470 --> 05:06.406
Let me direct one
of your reality shows.

05:06.439 --> 05:07.975
Also complicated.

05:08.009 --> 05:08.910
You don't have the credits,

05:08.943 --> 05:10.211
you know I can't do that.

05:10.244 --> 05:13.381
If you gave me a show
I'd have the credits.

05:13.413 --> 05:16.183
If it were up to
me, I would, really.

05:16.217 --> 05:17.652
But it's not, I have bosses.

05:18.686 --> 05:19.654
Go back to anime.

05:22.489 --> 05:23.324
I just can't.

05:25.159 --> 05:26.327
Then I can't help you.

05:27.328 --> 05:28.595
I'm leaving.

05:28.629 --> 05:30.331
Okay.

05:30.364 --> 05:31.799
Bye.

05:31.832 --> 05:32.833
Bye.

05:32.867 --> 05:33.768
Bye.

05:33.801 --> 05:34.702
You okay?

05:35.937 --> 05:36.938
Fine, I just like,

05:38.005 --> 05:39.140
do you have any Xanax?

05:39.173 --> 05:40.908
I have like no
insurance right now.

05:40.942 --> 05:43.644
Yeah, left-hand
side, middle drawer.

05:44.577 --> 05:46.247
How many do you need?

05:46.280 --> 05:47.815
As many as you can spare.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.183
Okay, well
don't take the whole thing.

05:49.216 --> 05:51.819
I need them until the
kids are back to school.

05:51.852 --> 05:52.653
Good?

05:52.687 --> 05:54.288
Okay, take those.

05:55.957 --> 05:57.457
Why do you need so much Xanax?

05:58.392 --> 06:00.094
Well I don't know, Heather.

06:00.127 --> 06:02.263
Why would I need Xanax?

06:02.296 --> 06:04.265
Okay well, just be careful.

06:06.233 --> 06:07.234
Bye buddy.

06:07.268 --> 06:08.836
Bye.

06:08.869 --> 06:09.937
What's my name?

06:09.971 --> 06:10.905
Nimoy.

06:10.938 --> 06:12.807
Say, Uncle Jeffrey.

06:12.840 --> 06:13.674
Nimoy!

06:14.809 --> 06:15.943
Leonard Nimoy.

06:18.980 --> 06:19.880
Love you, buddy.

06:19.914 --> 06:22.582
Bye, love you too, bye.

06:22.616 --> 06:23.451
Bye.

06:24.919 --> 06:25.753
Eat something.

06:36.864 --> 06:38.132
This is Jeff.

06:38.165 --> 06:40.567
Hello, I'm
looking for Jeff Nimoy?

06:40.601 --> 06:42.003
Who's this?

06:42.036 --> 06:44.238
Kyle Bailey,
I'm with Geek Kon.

06:44.271 --> 06:47.008
Oh, hi.

06:47.041 --> 06:49.110
Am I catching
you at a bad time?

06:49.143 --> 06:51.679
Oh, no.

06:51.712 --> 06:53.381
Great, well
if you remember,

06:53.414 --> 06:55.216
we had you at our
anime convention

06:55.249 --> 06:57.418
here in Madison, Wisconsin
about 10 years ago,

06:57.451 --> 06:58.886
and we were wondering
if you'd like

06:58.919 --> 07:01.521
to be a VIP guest
again this weekend?

07:01.554 --> 07:02.957
This weekend?

07:02.990 --> 07:05.558
Yeah, we had a voice
director recently cancel

07:05.592 --> 07:07.228
and we need a big name

07:07.261 --> 07:10.031
for our voice acting
workshop and director panel.

07:10.064 --> 07:11.966
Are you available?

07:11.999 --> 07:16.437
I don't know, I don't really
do anime conventions anymore.

07:16.470 --> 07:19.006
In fact, I think the
last one I did was yours,

07:19.040 --> 07:20.441
10 years ago.

07:20.474 --> 07:22.309
Well, cons have
certainly changed since then.

07:22.343 --> 07:23.543
Oh yeah?

07:23.576 --> 07:25.112
From what I remember
it's just a free trip

07:25.146 --> 07:26.714
to meet a handful of fans.

07:26.747 --> 07:28.783
Well, true
the trip is free,

07:28.816 --> 07:31.352
like all cons we provide
your airfare and hotel room,

07:31.385 --> 07:33.988
but you may not realize
that now cons do things...

07:34.021 --> 07:36.023
Plus you know,
anime conventions,

07:36.057 --> 07:38.959
there's all that
handshaking, and hugging.

07:40.127 --> 07:41.929
Lots of germ transference.

07:41.962 --> 07:45.166
Well, one change is
we supply hand sanitizer now,

07:45.199 --> 07:46.967
so I don't think
you need to worry.

07:48.402 --> 07:51.205
Yeah, well unless there's
some other major changes,

07:51.238 --> 07:53.474
I think it's a hard pass.

07:53.507 --> 07:55.443
Well, I was
trying to tell you,

07:55.476 --> 07:58.212
the major change is we
now pay appearance fees.

07:58.245 --> 08:00.314
Cons are a lot bigger
than they used to be.

08:00.347 --> 08:02.850
How does three
thousand dollars sound?

08:04.285 --> 08:05.286
Mister Nimoy?

08:06.454 --> 08:07.988
Mister Nimoy?

08:08.022 --> 08:10.724
Oh, you wanted Jeff Nimoy?

08:12.927 --> 08:15.362
Hold on, let me get him.

08:23.737 --> 08:25.306
Jeff Nimoy.

08:46.393 --> 08:48.162
Hi, I'm Jeff Nimoy.

08:49.029 --> 08:50.297
Yes, I know.

08:50.331 --> 08:53.100
I recognize you from
your Wikipedia page.

08:53.134 --> 08:54.034
What's your name?

08:54.068 --> 08:55.803
Oh of course, I'm Bobbi.

08:55.836 --> 08:57.037
Hi Bobbi, nice to meet you.

08:57.071 --> 08:58.973
Nice to meet you.

08:59.006 --> 08:59.974
Shall we go?

09:00.007 --> 09:01.742
Oh, sorry I'm nervous.

09:01.775 --> 09:03.612
I just have never met
a big star before.

09:03.644 --> 09:05.346
It's okay, I'm
not such a big star.

09:05.379 --> 09:06.547
Don't be nervous.

09:06.580 --> 09:09.283
Yes you are, you're like
the Steven Spielberg of anime.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.820
Okay, at least the
Ed Wood of anime.

09:14.221 --> 09:15.923
Can I get your bag?

09:15.956 --> 09:17.158
No, don't be silly.

09:17.191 --> 09:19.226
No, you are a VIP,
you deserve the best.

09:20.227 --> 09:21.061
Okay.

09:23.030 --> 09:25.199
Trigun is like
my favorite anime,

09:25.232 --> 09:26.734
and Wolfwood is definitely

09:26.767 --> 09:28.169
my favorite character
of all time.

09:28.202 --> 09:31.138
When he died I cried
like a little baby.

09:31.172 --> 09:34.041
I cried too, when he
died I was out of a job.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.443
Of course I prefer the
Japanese sub-titled version,

09:36.477 --> 09:38.112
but I don't think
that Sho Hayami

09:38.145 --> 09:39.313
did as good of a job

09:39.346 --> 09:40.915
at capturing Wolfwood's
essence as you did.

09:40.948 --> 09:42.383
And your voice is much smokier,

09:42.416 --> 09:43.784
which makes sense,

09:43.817 --> 09:45.686
because as you know
Wolfwood is a chain-smoker.

09:45.719 --> 09:47.656
You know, that
bag is on rollers.

09:47.688 --> 09:49.924
You could just put
it down and pull it.

09:50.925 --> 09:51.825
Of course.

09:51.859 --> 09:53.861
Yeah, that's how it works.

09:53.894 --> 09:55.362
Been that way for a long time.

09:55.396 --> 09:56.697
Anyway, what an amazing
character Wolfwood was,

09:56.730 --> 09:58.899
I mean a hard-drinking,
chain-smoking,

09:58.933 --> 10:01.035
womanizing, perverted priest.

10:01.068 --> 10:02.303
Typecasting I guess.

10:03.904 --> 10:05.739
Wolfwood is 30, or maybe 40,

10:07.007 --> 10:08.242
the characteristic
art style emerged...

10:08.275 --> 10:09.644
Oh, Mister Nimoy!

10:09.678 --> 10:10.844
You made it!

10:10.878 --> 10:12.146
Kyle Bailey, we
spoke on the phone.

10:12.179 --> 10:13.214
Hi Kyle.

10:17.451 --> 10:18.653
I see you met Bobbi.

10:18.687 --> 10:20.187
Oh yes.

10:20.221 --> 10:22.823
She's quite the
encyclopedia of anime.

10:22.856 --> 10:24.091
I'm a bit of a savant.

10:25.292 --> 10:27.728
Bobbi will be your
handler all weekend.

10:27.761 --> 10:28.596
Great.

10:30.431 --> 10:33.267
So is this pretty much
the way you remember it?

10:35.502 --> 10:36.537
It smells the same.

10:37.905 --> 10:41.041
When you wear the same
costume for four days in a row,

10:41.075 --> 10:43.544
sometimes things tend
to get a little, ripe.

10:43.577 --> 10:44.511
Yeah.

10:44.545 --> 10:46.313
We call that, otaku funk.

10:47.682 --> 10:48.949
Lovely.

10:48.983 --> 10:50.985
It gets far worse by Sunday.

10:51.018 --> 10:53.187
As will my germophobia.

10:53.220 --> 10:55.589
But I guess for 3000 dollars
I can put up with it.

10:55.624 --> 10:57.391
As long as they
don't try to hug me.

10:58.792 --> 10:59.593
They will.

10:59.628 --> 11:00.427
They will.

11:04.431 --> 11:05.232
Hey,

11:06.400 --> 11:09.303
can I possibly,
can I get my check?

11:10.471 --> 11:12.741
Yes, of course, I'm so sorry.

11:15.242 --> 11:15.976
That's not it.

11:17.378 --> 11:18.946
That I even have to ask.

11:18.979 --> 11:19.780
There you go buddy.

11:19.813 --> 11:21.148
Thanks, I'm sorry.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.483
A little bit embarrassing.

11:22.516 --> 11:24.084
No, no problem,
no problem at all.

11:24.118 --> 11:27.321
Okay, so you seem
to be taken care of.

11:27.354 --> 11:28.222
Enjoy your stay.

11:28.255 --> 11:29.056
Thanks.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.157
I hope you like your room.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.259
Thanks very much.

11:32.293 --> 11:32.993
Shall we?

11:33.027 --> 11:34.128
Yeah, it'll be just a sec.

11:34.161 --> 11:35.296
The elevator.

11:35.329 --> 11:36.765
Thanks.

11:36.797 --> 11:38.633
Okay so, this is your room.

11:38.667 --> 11:39.900
Okay.

11:39.933 --> 11:41.235
And you have my number,

11:41.268 --> 11:44.338
so if you need anything
just text me, call me.

11:44.371 --> 11:45.607
Do you need anything?

11:45.640 --> 11:48.610
Not unless you have
any Xanax.

11:48.643 --> 11:49.977
Sure.

11:50.010 --> 11:51.278
How many do you need?

11:52.146 --> 11:54.081
As many as you can spare.

11:54.114 --> 11:56.250
Take the whole thing,
I've got more at home.

11:57.686 --> 11:58.485
Gee thanks.

11:58.519 --> 11:59.621
No problem.

11:59.654 --> 12:01.690
Do you need anything else?

12:01.723 --> 12:03.457
I don't, but if I do,

12:03.490 --> 12:05.492
I'll call you, or text you.

12:05.526 --> 12:06.460
Okay.

12:06.493 --> 12:07.494
Okay, I've got your number.

12:07.528 --> 12:08.329
Yeah.

12:08.362 --> 12:09.163
Okay, goodnight.

12:09.196 --> 12:09.997
Bye.

12:11.598 --> 12:12.734
You're gonna
watch me go inside?

12:12.767 --> 12:13.967
Yeah, I just want to make sure

12:14.001 --> 12:15.235
you get in okay, that's my job.

12:15.269 --> 12:16.738
Sure, okay.

12:16.771 --> 12:18.138
I've been going through
doors since I'm 30 though,

12:18.172 --> 12:19.406
so I know what I'm doing.

12:19.440 --> 12:21.075
I know, sometimes
the keys are tricky.

12:21.108 --> 12:22.343
Okay, goodbye.

12:22.376 --> 12:23.410
Bye.

12:23.444 --> 12:24.278
Sleep well.

12:24.311 --> 12:25.479
Okay.

12:25.512 --> 12:27.181
Don't let the lady
spiders bite.

12:28.315 --> 12:29.116
Goodbye.

12:29.149 --> 12:29.983
Bye.

12:31.753 --> 12:33.921
But you're still here
is what I'm saying.

12:35.055 --> 12:36.056
I'll go.

12:36.090 --> 12:36.890
I just.

12:36.924 --> 12:37.726
Goodnight.

12:37.759 --> 12:38.559
Goodnight.

12:38.592 --> 12:39.493
Sorry.

12:39.526 --> 12:40.695
You've got a room
too though, don't you?

12:40.729 --> 12:41.395
Yeah, yeah.

12:41.428 --> 12:42.463
Okay I'll see you later.

12:42.496 --> 12:43.297
Okay.

12:43.330 --> 12:44.131
Okay bye.

12:44.164 --> 12:44.965
Okay bye.

12:44.998 --> 12:45.800
Go away.

12:45.834 --> 12:46.668
Goodbye.

13:53.500 --> 13:57.171
Hello Madison Geek
Kon, how you doing?

13:58.939 --> 13:59.973
Good to see you again.

14:00.007 --> 14:01.175
You too, man.

14:01.208 --> 14:03.310
Did you know you were the
first actor I ever hired in LA?

14:03.343 --> 14:04.813
No way, really?

14:04.846 --> 14:05.946
You mean that Arnold
Schwarzenegger thing?

14:05.979 --> 14:07.114
Oh my God you remember it?

14:07.147 --> 14:08.348
Of course I do.

14:08.382 --> 14:10.050
It was Arnold
Schwarzenegger as,

14:10.951 --> 14:12.152
he was a short order cook.

14:12.186 --> 14:13.420
It's like, put
down the short ribs,

14:13.454 --> 14:14.689
what are you doing?

14:14.722 --> 14:16.858
That's not barbecue
sauce, it's blood.

14:16.891 --> 14:19.226
You remember every
line, it's insane.

14:19.259 --> 14:21.061
Of course man,
that was a classic.

14:21.094 --> 14:21.896
Oh my God.

14:21.930 --> 14:23.564
All two episodes.

14:23.597 --> 14:25.199
I'm surprised it
lasted that long.

14:25.232 --> 14:26.066
I know.

14:27.301 --> 14:28.469
Do you do many cons?

14:28.502 --> 14:30.504
Yeah yeah, I do
quite a few actually.

14:30.537 --> 14:31.673
I do this one every year.

14:31.706 --> 14:32.640
Oh really?

14:32.674 --> 14:34.141
Yeah, I've got some
family here in Madison,

14:34.174 --> 14:35.409
so it's a good excuse for me

14:35.442 --> 14:36.811
to get a free trip
to see everybody.

14:36.845 --> 14:38.045
That's smart, good for you.

14:38.078 --> 14:39.279
I miss working with you.

14:39.313 --> 14:41.081
You too man, it's been great.

14:41.114 --> 14:42.784
No one will hire me.

14:43.651 --> 14:44.551
Oh shit, that's me.

14:44.585 --> 14:46.019
I gotta go, see you later.

14:50.557 --> 14:54.094
Whoa, has it been
a year already?

14:57.030 --> 14:59.366
Damn, they'll let
anybody in here.

14:59.399 --> 15:00.735
Jeff Nimoy!

15:02.637 --> 15:03.805
Brian Donovan.

15:03.838 --> 15:05.439
Oh my God, I can't believe it.

15:05.472 --> 15:07.541
Dude, what rock did you
crawl out from under?

15:07.574 --> 15:08.475
How long has it been, man?

15:08.509 --> 15:09.811
I don't know, when did we wrap

15:09.844 --> 15:12.346
that crappy anime series
I directed you in?

15:12.379 --> 15:14.448
Don't laugh too hard,
it's still on TV somewhere.

15:14.481 --> 15:16.918
That's why I keep getting
invited to these things.

15:18.085 --> 15:20.120
We polished that
turd pretty good then.

15:22.055 --> 15:23.390
Hey man, I've been
looking around.

15:23.423 --> 15:25.425
I can't believe how
the money's changed.

15:25.459 --> 15:27.394
There's like some serious
big business going on here.

15:27.427 --> 15:28.428
Tell me about it, brother.

15:28.462 --> 15:29.664
This is all I do know.

15:29.697 --> 15:31.131
Really?

15:31.164 --> 15:32.499
Seriously man, I travel
almost every weekend,

15:32.533 --> 15:33.668
and I make a fortune.

15:33.701 --> 15:35.202
Dude, sign me up.

15:35.235 --> 15:36.136
Right?

15:36.169 --> 15:37.705
No I'm not kidding, I need it.

15:37.739 --> 15:39.439
Hello, Brian Donovan.

15:39.473 --> 15:40.340
Hey you.

15:42.142 --> 15:43.778
I was wondering
when I'd see you.

15:43.811 --> 15:45.279
Hey Jeff, do you
know Nikki Boyer?

15:45.312 --> 15:46.213
No I don't.

15:46.246 --> 15:47.147
Nik, this is Jeff Nimoy.

15:47.180 --> 15:48.716
Yeah, of course I know you.

15:48.750 --> 15:51.986
I'm your biggest fan.

15:52.020 --> 15:52.854
Yeah, right?

15:54.856 --> 15:56.123
Oh, she's being serious.

15:56.156 --> 15:58.225
Oh I'm sorry, that's sweet.

15:58.258 --> 15:59.526
Thank you.

15:59.560 --> 16:00.695
No seriously,

16:00.728 --> 16:01.829
I really am.

16:01.863 --> 16:02.997
Why don't you work more?

16:03.031 --> 16:03.865
Oh, burn.

16:05.033 --> 16:06.868
No no, that is
not what I meant.

16:06.901 --> 16:07.769
Oh God.

16:07.802 --> 16:08.736
That's what she meant.

16:08.770 --> 16:10.270
No it's okay, I
know what you meant,

16:10.304 --> 16:11.438
don't listen to him.

16:12.172 --> 16:14.141
Mister Brian Donovan.

16:14.174 --> 16:15.576
Oh shit, that's me.

16:15.610 --> 16:16.778
Bye.

16:20.815 --> 16:23.952
What do you say,
Madison, Wisconsin?

16:23.985 --> 16:24.819
Geek Kon.

16:29.423 --> 16:30.925
So, you're an actress?

16:30.959 --> 16:33.061
Yeah, a voice actress.

16:33.093 --> 16:33.928
Yeah I.

16:34.829 --> 16:36.229
Right.

16:36.263 --> 16:39.601
Sorry, I get a little
flustered around celebrities.

16:39.634 --> 16:41.970
Oh come on, you really
think I'm a celebrity?

16:43.136 --> 16:45.940
Yeah, you're like
the biggest name here.

16:45.974 --> 16:46.975
Get outta here.

