32:33.688 --> 32:35.155
to meet like this, one-on-one.

32:35.188 --> 32:37.025
Yeah well, I'm not
seeing any of it.

32:37.057 --> 32:39.661
Yeah you are,
they pay to be here.

32:39.694 --> 32:40.662
Not enough.

32:50.838 --> 32:52.907
I wouldn't get too close
to him if I were you.

32:52.941 --> 32:53.775
To who?

32:54.742 --> 32:56.778
You know, Mister Kissy Face.

32:58.345 --> 32:59.781
Oh my God, are you jealous?

33:01.114 --> 33:02.617
Maybe.

33:02.650 --> 33:04.184
But seriously, I heard he plowed

33:04.217 --> 33:06.520
like a million girls back
in the old days, on tour.

33:08.155 --> 33:10.290
Like you've
never hit on a fan?

33:10.324 --> 33:11.124
A million and one,

33:11.158 --> 33:12.694
but I'm just saying.

33:12.727 --> 33:14.062
Well, maybe he's changed.

33:15.295 --> 33:16.931
Doubtful, I saw him
leaving this afternoon's

33:16.965 --> 33:19.067
autograph session
with a young hottie.

33:19.099 --> 33:21.201
Obviously a little Con nooner.

33:22.269 --> 33:23.671
Don't spread rumors, Brian.

33:23.705 --> 33:24.606
That's not cool.

33:24.639 --> 33:26.173
Fine, ask him yourself.

33:26.206 --> 33:27.541
Fine, I will.

33:29.911 --> 33:31.012
Okay.

33:31.045 --> 33:32.245
Yeah.

33:32.279 --> 33:34.015
I'll be here when you
come crawling back.

33:39.053 --> 33:40.454
Hey, how's it going man?

33:40.487 --> 33:41.656
Well if it isn't Jeff Nimoy.

33:41.689 --> 33:44.157
Oh, how'd you kn...
oh, you cheated.

33:44.191 --> 33:46.094
I swear to God I didn't.

33:46.126 --> 33:47.160
How's it going?

33:47.194 --> 33:48.161
- Good.
- What's your name?

33:48.195 --> 33:48.963
- Brandon.
- Brandon,

33:48.997 --> 33:49.631
okay, how's it going?

33:50.832 --> 33:54.201
Can I get a, oh a club
soda please, thanks.

33:54.234 --> 33:55.435
That's it?

33:55.469 --> 33:56.269
Yeah.

33:56.303 --> 33:57.170
Come on,

33:57.204 --> 33:58.438
Mister Nimoy we've
got a full bar,

33:58.472 --> 33:59.874
you can get anything you'd like.

33:59.907 --> 34:03.176
Oh, oh, okay in that
case I'll have a club soda.

34:04.344 --> 34:05.245
Comin' right up.

34:05.278 --> 34:06.380
Thanks man, I appreciate it.

34:06.413 --> 34:07.314
Hi.

34:07.347 --> 34:08.447
Oh hey, how's it going?

34:08.482 --> 34:09.684
Good.

34:09.717 --> 34:11.719
How about that
panel today, huh?

34:11.753 --> 34:12.552
Yeah.

34:13.420 --> 34:14.487
How about that kiss?

34:15.422 --> 34:16.156
Sorry.

34:16.188 --> 34:17.556
No, don't be.

34:17.591 --> 34:21.228
It was fantastic, the highlight
of that hour, for sure.

34:22.630 --> 34:24.732
Oh, how much do
I owe you buddy?

34:24.766 --> 34:27.601
Oh, nothing for VIP guests,

34:27.635 --> 34:29.704
only the fans and
staff have to pay.

34:29.737 --> 34:30.570
Really?

34:30.605 --> 34:31.505
Yeah.

34:31.538 --> 34:32.572
Can I get you anything?

34:32.607 --> 34:33.373
I'm good.

34:33.407 --> 34:34.574
It's on me.

34:34.609 --> 34:35.842
No, thanks though.

34:35.877 --> 34:36.744
Pretty generous of me.

34:36.777 --> 34:37.577
Yeah, pretty generous.

34:37.612 --> 34:38.445
I'm a giver.

34:40.114 --> 34:41.014
So?

34:41.049 --> 34:43.051
So, can I ask you a question?

34:43.083 --> 34:44.284
Shoot.

34:44.317 --> 34:46.319
What's your stance
on sleeping with fans?

34:49.222 --> 34:50.024
I'm sorry.

34:52.126 --> 34:53.193
Wow, didn't expect that.

34:53.226 --> 34:54.293
Caught you off-guard, huh?

34:54.327 --> 34:57.130
Well, to tell you the truth,

34:57.165 --> 34:59.701
in the old days I
was quite for it.

34:59.734 --> 35:01.169
But now that I'm older,

35:01.201 --> 35:04.605
I don't foresee myself
doing much of it anymore.

35:04.639 --> 35:05.840
Really?

35:05.873 --> 35:07.340
Really.

35:07.374 --> 35:09.443
So what about that girl in
your autograph line today?

35:11.244 --> 35:14.015
That time it really
did come out of my nose.

35:14.048 --> 35:15.582
Are you stalking
me, Nikki Boyer?

35:15.616 --> 35:17.151
Maybe.

35:17.185 --> 35:18.019
Okay.

35:20.088 --> 35:21.055
I thought about it.

35:22.123 --> 35:23.323
I thought about it hard.

35:24.491 --> 35:27.294
But in the end it wasn't
as hard as I thought,

35:28.730 --> 35:29.596
to turn her down.

35:31.065 --> 35:32.432
Good.

35:32.466 --> 35:34.102
Good.

35:34.135 --> 35:35.136
You know, we met before.

35:35.169 --> 35:37.105
Oh, did we?

35:37.138 --> 35:38.639
Did you audition
for me or something?

35:38.673 --> 35:40.675
No, it was actually at a con.

35:40.708 --> 35:42.110
A con?

35:42.143 --> 35:43.644
Yeah, back in Saint Louis,
that's where I'm from.

35:43.678 --> 35:44.979
Oh wow, Saint Louis?

35:45.012 --> 35:46.346
That must have been
a long time ago.

35:46.379 --> 35:49.617
Yeah, gosh it was
like 15 years ago.

35:49.650 --> 35:51.418
Wow, you must have
been like a kid?

35:51.451 --> 35:53.286
Well I was graduated
from college.

35:53.320 --> 35:54.622
And you were already
a voice actress?

35:54.655 --> 35:55.857
No, not yet.

35:55.890 --> 35:57.457
I was attending
the con as a fan.

35:59.160 --> 36:00.527
Wait a minute.

36:00.560 --> 36:02.830
My sleeping with fans,

36:02.864 --> 36:04.132
all this line of questioning,

36:04.165 --> 36:06.701
did we like make
out or something?

36:06.734 --> 36:07.668
No no.

36:07.702 --> 36:08.870
And you're busting me?

36:08.903 --> 36:10.705
- No.
- All these years later.

36:10.738 --> 36:12.640
All right, I'll take
your word for it.

36:13.841 --> 36:16.110
But, I was a big fan of yours.

36:17.044 --> 36:18.345
Still am I guess.

36:19.479 --> 36:20.313
Cheers to that.

36:21.448 --> 36:23.151
Anyway, I remember
that you stayed

36:23.184 --> 36:24.752
way after an autograph
session was over,

36:24.786 --> 36:26.319
to make sure that
each fan got one.

36:26.353 --> 36:29.523
Must have been like five hours?

36:29.556 --> 36:31.692
Huh, I kind of remember that.

36:31.726 --> 36:33.194
And you didn't charge a cent,

36:33.227 --> 36:34.662
it was totally free.

36:36.164 --> 36:38.666
I guess it's different
circumstances for me now.

36:40.367 --> 36:41.501
I'm sorry about that.

36:42.703 --> 36:44.939
Hope you made a lot of money.

36:44.972 --> 36:47.541
I did actually,
like a small fortune.

36:47.574 --> 36:48.810
Well, good for you.

36:48.843 --> 36:50.310
I mean look, it's not
a bad thing to charge,

36:50.343 --> 36:52.345
and I do it sometimes when
the other actors ask me to,

36:52.379 --> 36:53.781
but I usually end up

36:53.815 --> 36:55.850
giving the money to
charity or something.

36:57.185 --> 36:58.953
Well if it makes
you feel any better,

36:58.986 --> 37:00.487
the Jeff Foundation
is taking care

37:00.520 --> 37:02.857
of poor impoverished
voice directors,

37:02.890 --> 37:03.991
and paying their rent.

37:06.493 --> 37:09.063
Can I ask you
another question?

37:09.096 --> 37:11.364
What till I swallow.

37:11.398 --> 37:12.633
All right, go.

37:12.667 --> 37:14.501
Why do you need
the money so bad?

37:14.534 --> 37:15.970
Oh geez.

37:16.003 --> 37:17.238
Don't be shy Nikki Boyer,

37:17.271 --> 37:19.372
ask me a real personal
question next time.

37:21.843 --> 37:22.810
It's a long story.

37:24.145 --> 37:25.746
Maybe after a few
more club sodas

37:25.780 --> 37:27.782
I'll loosen up and tell you.

37:27.815 --> 37:29.349
Okay, that's fair enough.

37:31.484 --> 37:32.887
Want to walk around the con?

37:32.920 --> 37:34.454
Yeah, great idea.

37:34.487 --> 37:35.957
Let's go.

37:35.990 --> 37:38.292
Hey man, for the tip jar.

37:38.326 --> 37:39.126
Oh, thanks.

37:39.160 --> 37:40.628
Thanks buddy.

37:40.661 --> 37:42.096
Easiest drink I'll have
to remember all weekend.

38:10.725 --> 38:13.593
You don't really like
the fans very much, do you?

38:13.628 --> 38:15.329
No, I do, I do.

38:15.363 --> 38:17.430
They just get a little
crazy sometimes,

38:17.464 --> 38:18.866
don't you think?

38:18.900 --> 38:20.868
No not really, I
actually think it's cool,

38:20.902 --> 38:23.037
because they're
usually outsiders,

38:23.070 --> 38:24.272
and they feel like
they don't fit in,

38:24.305 --> 38:25.773
and I'm sure some of
them are even bullied,

38:25.806 --> 38:28.276
or made fun of for
liking cosplay so much,

38:28.309 --> 38:31.312
but here it's not like that.

38:31.345 --> 38:32.980
I never thought
of it that way.

38:33.014 --> 38:34.015
Yeah, you're right.

38:34.048 --> 38:37.084
This place is pretty nice.

38:37.118 --> 38:39.053
I haven't been this
relaxed in forever.

38:40.254 --> 38:41.454
Relaxed is good.

38:42.690 --> 38:44.491
Stress will kill you.

38:44.524 --> 38:45.359
Oh yeah.

38:47.228 --> 38:49.562
I've also been a little
depressed lately.

38:49.596 --> 38:51.098
Well that's not good.

38:51.132 --> 38:53.566
No, it's like
very not good, okay?

38:53.601 --> 38:54.835
Believe me.

38:54.869 --> 38:56.637
Take the opposite of good, okay.

38:56.671 --> 38:57.872
What's the opposite of good?

38:57.905 --> 38:59.240
Not good, that's the
opposite of good.

38:59.273 --> 39:00.573
But that's good.

39:01.709 --> 39:03.244
I thought we'd do
the greatest tremendous

39:03.277 --> 39:05.913
most tremendous impersonations
of all time, okay?

39:05.947 --> 39:07.949
Probably the greatest
impersonator ever.

39:10.117 --> 39:11.152
Who else do you do?

39:12.119 --> 39:14.221
I do Herve Villechaize.

39:14.255 --> 39:15.156
Hello boss.

39:16.390 --> 39:17.758
I don't know who that is.

39:17.792 --> 39:20.460
Da plane, da plane!

39:20.493 --> 39:21.295
No.

39:21.329 --> 39:22.363
Fantasy Island.

39:22.396 --> 39:24.131
I think it's before my time.

39:26.300 --> 39:28.336
How dare you?

39:28.369 --> 39:29.469
How dare you?

39:30.604 --> 39:32.740
See, how can you stay
depressed around me?

39:33.808 --> 39:34.709
I guess I can't.

39:36.077 --> 39:37.611
I mean, how depressed are you?

39:39.947 --> 39:41.649
Not as depressed as
this guy, obviously.

39:44.085 --> 39:45.019
That's him.

39:46.187 --> 39:47.321
Depressed, depressed.

39:47.355 --> 39:48.656
Like suicidal?

39:48.689 --> 39:50.257
- No!
- That's good.

39:50.291 --> 39:51.392
Not today.

39:51.425 --> 39:52.827
Jeff?

39:52.860 --> 39:55.196
Well if I did die, no one's
life would be different.

39:56.797 --> 39:58.833
People would be sad.

39:58.866 --> 39:59.834
I would be sad.

40:01.002 --> 40:03.037
Yeah, you'll all be
sad for a little while.

40:03.070 --> 40:05.473
You know this guy'll be
sad for a minute or two.

40:05.505 --> 40:07.775
But no one's life will
physically change.

40:07.808 --> 40:09.777
I have no wife, no kids.

40:09.810 --> 40:11.145
It would be like
I was never here.

40:11.178 --> 40:12.013
Poof.

40:14.048 --> 40:15.850
There'd be no Digimon.

40:15.883 --> 40:17.385
Of course there would.

40:17.418 --> 40:19.220
I didn't create the show,
I was just a hired monkey.

40:19.253 --> 40:21.355
It's a fluke I even
worked in anime at all.

40:21.389 --> 40:23.556
I couldn't get
arrested as an actor.

40:23.590 --> 40:27.261
Then I booked a cheap little
VO job in anime one day,

40:27.294 --> 40:30.831
and then worked it into
writing and directing,

40:30.865 --> 40:34.635
then I got Digimon, and I've
been stuck in anime ever since.

40:34.668 --> 40:37.905
It's not a bad
place to be stuck.

40:37.938 --> 40:38.773
If you say so.

40:40.074 --> 40:41.342
Wow, you are depressed.

40:42.777 --> 40:43.611
I'll be okay.

40:45.246 --> 40:47.148
As long as you're here.

40:48.015 --> 40:49.183
But as soon as you leave,

40:49.216 --> 40:50.718
I'll be depressed again.

40:52.319 --> 40:54.889
Well I guess I'd
better not leave then.

40:57.557 --> 40:59.794
Well, be careful
what you wish for.

41:03.030 --> 41:04.632
It's getting late.

41:04.665 --> 41:05.565
Let's get going.

41:08.536 --> 41:09.970
Later than I think.

41:10.004 --> 41:10.805
Oh!

41:13.741 --> 41:14.542
Hate you.

41:17.344 --> 41:19.080
Meanwhile, at the
hall of justice.

41:24.418 --> 41:27.388
Well, this is me.

41:27.421 --> 41:28.622
Okay.

41:28.656 --> 41:30.091
Thanks for today.

41:30.124 --> 41:33.027
I had a really good time.

41:33.961 --> 41:34.795
Me too.

41:36.230 --> 41:38.199
Wanna come in for a nightcap?

41:38.232 --> 41:39.700
I thought you didn't drink?

41:40.935 --> 41:42.470
All right, you busted me.

41:43.471 --> 41:45.506
You did promise not to leave me.

41:45.539 --> 41:48.642
Oh promise is kind
of a strong word.

41:50.744 --> 41:53.013
I just don't want
the night to end.

41:53.047 --> 41:56.317
Are you sure your depression
can handle more fun?

41:56.350 --> 42:01.355
I can handle more of that
kiss you gave me today.

42:08.229 --> 42:10.364
Maybe I'll come to
your room tomorrow.

42:14.201 --> 42:15.202
Tomorrow, huh?

42:15.236 --> 42:15.970
Yeah.

42:18.272 --> 42:20.908
But I never said anything
about my room tonight.

42:25.212 --> 42:26.046
Okay.

43:28.075 --> 43:29.410
Yes!

43:29.443 --> 43:30.377
Yes!

43:39.587 --> 43:40.821
You can get some shrimp?

43:40.854 --> 43:43.190
Yes, I can get some shrimp.

43:45.259 --> 43:47.094
Okay well.

43:47.127 --> 43:48.495
He must really
want some shrimp.

43:48.529 --> 43:50.164
Voice actors love shrimp.

43:50.197 --> 43:53.200
I think they, maybe they
expect that on the set.

43:53.234 --> 43:54.068
All the time.

43:57.371 --> 44:00.107
Well look what the cat
from Trigun dragged in.

44:00.140 --> 44:01.175
Hello Kitty.

44:01.208 --> 44:02.576
Good morning.

44:02.611 --> 44:04.812
You look well rested.

44:04.845 --> 44:06.413
Thank you.

44:06.447 --> 44:07.682
Sleep well?

44:07.716 --> 44:08.617
Reasonably.

44:08.650 --> 44:10.017
You?

44:10.050 --> 44:10.951
Very well, thanks.

44:10.985 --> 44:12.253
Although I didn't have anyone

44:12.286 --> 44:14.021
to keep me warm last
night like you did.

44:14.054 --> 44:15.856
Are you stalking me, Brian?

44:15.889 --> 44:17.791
No, but I can tell
by your reaction

44:17.825 --> 44:20.527
that you were with
Nimoy last night, ha.

44:20.561 --> 44:22.329
Ha ha, not funny.

44:22.363 --> 44:23.797
No, not ha ha funny,

44:23.831 --> 44:25.966
ha ha the joke's on you.

44:26.000 --> 44:27.401
Don't say I didn't warn you.

44:28.435 --> 44:30.004
Good morning, all.

44:30.037 --> 44:30.938
Hi.

44:30.971 --> 44:31.805
Good morning.

44:31.839 --> 44:32.973
What's up?

44:33.007 --> 44:34.241
Hey, try the
sausages, Nikki did.

44:34.275 --> 44:35.242
This little one's
the perfect size.

44:35.276 --> 44:36.310
You're so juvenile.

44:37.211 --> 44:38.112
What was that all about?

44:38.145 --> 44:39.146
It's not worth it.

44:40.615 --> 44:42.082
Neither is this breakfast.

44:42.116 --> 44:44.551
Plus I don't see any food
handlers wearing gloves.

44:44.585 --> 44:46.053
I have a better idea.

44:46.086 --> 44:48.289
Why don't I buy you breakfast
downstairs with my per diem?

44:48.322 --> 44:48.989
Yes, indeed-em.

44:49.023 --> 44:50.224
All right, it's nice to have

44:50.257 --> 44:51.760
some money in my
pocket for once.

44:55.996 --> 44:57.398
You were too perfect.

45:07.642 --> 45:10.911
I will have a waffle, and
a side of sausage please.

45:10.944 --> 45:12.781
Great, could I
get you guys started

45:12.813 --> 45:14.882
with some mimosas
or bloody mary's?

45:14.915 --> 45:16.950
Ooh, I'll actually
have a bloody Mary,

45:16.984 --> 45:17.885
extra spicy please.

45:17.918 --> 45:19.520
Excellent, and you sir?

45:19.553 --> 45:21.055
I'm good with
just coffee, thanks.

45:21.088 --> 45:22.222
I'll be right back.

45:22.256 --> 45:24.158
So, tell me
about this new job.

45:24.191 --> 45:26.527
Oh, so it's an
interview for a producer

45:26.560 --> 45:30.197
of like "Best Beach Paradises,"
or some crap like that.

45:30.230 --> 45:31.031
That's great.

45:31.065 --> 45:32.667
So you love the beach.

45:32.701 --> 45:35.869
Yeah, yeah, but more importantly
it's a job in reality TV,

45:35.903 --> 45:38.038
and if I can build
my reality TV resume,

45:38.072 --> 45:39.808
I can hit up my
bigshot brother-in-law

45:39.840 --> 45:42.276
the reality TV
producer, for a gig.

45:42.309 --> 45:43.745
- Great!
- Yeah.

45:43.778 --> 45:45.012
Well, fingers crossed.

45:45.045 --> 45:46.280
Thank you.

45:46.313 --> 45:47.548
Here you go.

45:47.581 --> 45:48.415
Thank you.

45:50.217 --> 45:53.320
All right, to you
getting this job.

45:53.354 --> 45:54.188
Thank you.

45:57.324 --> 45:58.325
God, I need this job too,

45:58.359 --> 46:00.527
I haven't worked in forever.

46:00.561 --> 46:03.497
Why don't you just
go back to anime?

46:04.666 --> 46:05.599
It's complicated.

46:08.670 --> 46:10.337
You don't drink
at all, do you?

46:11.305 --> 46:13.340
Well, I used to,

46:13.374 --> 46:14.609
a little too much.

46:14.642 --> 46:16.977
Oh, is that a problem?

46:17.010 --> 46:17.846
It became one.

46:19.614 --> 46:20.948
The slightest little
emotional setback,

46:20.981 --> 46:22.751
and I reached for
the Jack Daniels.

46:22.784 --> 46:24.952
Hurricane Jeff would come
blowin' through town,

46:24.985 --> 46:26.688
destroying everything
in its wake.

46:27.588 --> 46:29.056
So when did it get bad?

46:29.089 --> 46:31.125
Oh yeah well,

46:31.158 --> 46:32.259
there was an incident.

46:36.263 --> 46:39.701
One drunken night I broke
into this recording studio,

46:39.734 --> 46:40.835
that was underpaying me.

46:40.869 --> 46:41.770
Uh oh.

46:41.803 --> 46:43.470
I had the
keys, I let myself in,

46:43.504 --> 46:45.807
but I started throwing
things around,

46:45.840 --> 46:47.241
messing with all the levels,

46:48.409 --> 46:51.011
but then I went a little
too far, even for me.

46:51.044 --> 46:53.013
Okay, what did you do?

46:53.046 --> 46:55.249
I took a dump
on the control panel.

46:56.917 --> 46:58.986
- No.
- Yes.

46:59.019 --> 46:59.821
You didn't?

46:59.854 --> 47:00.655
I did.

47:00.688 --> 47:01.522
That is so gross.

47:02.556 --> 47:04.391
I know, I know.

47:04.425 --> 47:06.059
It was terrible.

47:06.093 --> 47:08.095
I was fired the next day.

47:08.128 --> 47:10.264
The day after that,
I quit drinking.

47:11.131 --> 47:12.332
Smart.

47:12.366 --> 47:13.534
Not smart enough.

47:13.567 --> 47:16.403
I couldn't get arrested
in anime after that.

47:16.437 --> 47:19.306
That's the complicated
part I told you about.

47:19.339 --> 47:20.140
